Installed Ubuntu and nginx on VMware Workstation

What I did:
-Installed Ubuntu on VMware Workstation:
Fixed keyboard input issue by disabling USB

-Installed nginx:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nginx

-Started and stopped nginx:
sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo systemctl stop nginx

-Viewed site on localhost

-Accessed logs and observed activity being logged when accessing the site:
sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/access.log
Noticed no log activity when service is down

What I learned:
-How to install an operating system on a virtual machine
-nginx is a web server
-Services can be started and stopped
-Logs monitor activity
-No log activity is generated when a service is down
